<div class="row m-5">
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h1>Fitness Tracker App</h1>
    <p class="mt-3">The Fitness Tracker app is the solution to the common struggle of maintaining a consistent workout routine. With the ability to track workouts and monitor progress, users can stay on track to reach their fitness goals. The app offers a simple and user-friendly interface, making it accessible to anyone regardless of fitness level or experience. Users can add, edit, and delete workouts according to their preferences.</p>
    <p class="mt-3">Additionally, features such as the ability to track calories burned and workout duration allow users to easily monitor their progress and reach specific goals. By incorporating these features, we hope to cater to the needs of a wider range of users and provide a more comprehensive tracking experience.</p>
    <p class="mt-3 mb-5">Ultimately, the Fitness Tracker app aims to address the common challenges faced by those trying to maintain a consistent workout routine. By providing a simple and accessible solution, users can stay motivated, accountable, and on track to reach their fitness goals.</p>
    <%= link_to 'Create New', new_workout_path, class: 'btn btn-primary float-right' %>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-1">
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <h1>Workout History</h1>
    <table class="table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Name</th>
          <th>Date</th>
          <th>Calories burned</th>
          <th>Duration</th>
          <th colspan="3"></th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <% @workouts.each do |workout| %>
          <tr>
            <td><%= workout.name %></td>
            <td><%= workout.date %></td>
            <td><%= workout.caloriesburned %></td>
            <td><%= workout.duration %></td>
            <td>
              <div class="btn-group" role="group">
                <%= link_to 'Show', workout, class: 'btn btn-secondary' %>
                <%= link_to 'Edit', edit_workout_path(workout), class: 'btn btn-primary' %>
                <%= link_to 'Destroy', workout, method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' }, class: 'btn btn-danger' %>
              </div>
            </td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-1">
</div>